\date{2025-06-13}
\taxon{Lemma}
\title{Fully faithful functors reflect isomorphisms}
\import{base-macros}
\p{
	Let #{A\, B : \Cat} be categories and let #{F : A \to B} be a [fully faithful](0010) functor.
	Let #{x\,y : \ob(A)} be objects and #{f : A(x,y)} a morphism.
	If #{F(f) : B(f(x), f(y))} is [invertible](001R) then so is #{f}.
}
\proof{
	Immediate by either of the latter two [characterisations of invertibility](001R).
}
